ZH: 这个问题对于我来说，无异于一个考验。
EN: This question is, to me, no different than a challenge.

ZH: 在他眼中，我们的努力无异于白费。
EN: In his eyes, our efforts are no different than wasted.

ZH: 对于他来说，成功与失败无异。
EN: To him, success and failure are no different.

ZH: 这个工作对我来说，无异于是个噩梦。
EN: This job is, to me, no different than a nightmare.

ZH: 这种行为无异于对自己的辜负。
EN: Such behavior is no different than betraying oneself.

ZH: 在这个问题上，他的观点与我无异。
EN: On this issue, his opinion is no different than mine.

ZH: 我每天重复同样的工作，这无异于浪费生命。
EN: I repeat the same work every day, which is no different than wasting life.

ZH: 跟他相比，这些困难对我来说无异。
EN: Compared to him, these difficulties are no different than to me.

ZH: 对于他而言，你们的违法行为无异于背叛。
EN: To him, your illegal actions are no different than betrayal.

ZH: 对我来说，日本和韩国无异。
EN: To me, Japan and South Korea are no different.

ZH: 这次考试与以往的无异，我相信我会取得好成绩。
EN: This exam is no different than the previous ones, I believe I will achieve good results.

ZH: 睡在豪华的酒店和贫民窟无异。
EN: Sleeping in a luxury hotel is no different than in a slum.

ZH: 随便你说什么话，对我来说无异。
EN: Say whatever you want, it is no different than to me.

ZH: 她的死对他来说无异于世界末日。
EN: Her death is no different than the end of the world to him.

ZH: 在江湖这个世界中，生与死无异。
EN: In the world of the jianghu, life and death are no different.

ZH: 别人的批评无异于打了我的脸。
EN: Other people's criticism is no different than slapping me in the face.

ZH: 坐在这里还是站在那里无异。
EN: Sitting here or standing there is no different.

ZH: 穿一身特殊的制服无异于成为标靶。
EN: Wearing a special uniform is no different than becoming a target.

ZH: 无论你说什么，对我来说无异。
EN: Whatever you say, it is no different to me.

ZH: 在这个队伍里，胜利与失败无异。
EN: In this team, victory and defeat are no different.
